rust-proxmox-network-types (1.1.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * add a new `Fqdn` type for safely representing fully-qualified domain names
    that satisfy the relevant RFCs and Debian's hostname restrictions, moved
    out of pve-installer's common crate so it can be shared with other
    consumers.

  * api-types: add the api-type implementation for `Fqdn`.

  * api-types: add an api wrapper for `std::net::IpAddr`, matching the
    existing wrappers for `Ipv4Addr` and `Ipv6Addr`.

  * cidr: add a generic `IpAddr::new` constructor that takes either an IPv4 or
    an IPv6 address.

  * fqdn: implement `std::error::Error` for the parse-error type, so it
    interoperates cleanly with `anyhow` and other crates that rely on that
    trait for automatic error conversions.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 01:14:36 +0200

